<SLUG> BC-TECH-PLAYGEAR0801-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    InterAct accessory puts Sega to shame
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Reconfirming Sega's ineptitude in designing
interface devices for the Dreamcast console, InterAct Accessories
offers the TremorPak Plus ($20; www.interact-acc.com), an
all-in-one memory card and tactile feedback device that takes up
half the space in the controller (one slot for both functions)
while boasting the same amount of memory (200 blocks). More
importantly, the TremorPak Plus requires no batteries. It also has
no LCD screen, not that anyone seems to miss that private function.
It rumbles harder _ or ``jumps'' higher than Sega's equivalent, the
``Jump Pack'' _ and combines for $20 what Sega's two units do less
effectively for $50.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
