<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Still carrying a torch
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Follow the daily journey of the longest torch relay in
Olympics history from Olympia, Greece, to Olympic Park in Sydney,
Australia. There are thousands of torchbearers and about 50 modes
of transportation involved, including a scuba diver and a camel
(not at the same time, though). Read more about this incredible
journey at www.olympics.com/eng/about/torch/index.html
</P>
<P>
   HOT FRIES, COOL MUSIC
</P>
<P>
   Would you like a CD with that burger? Starting this week, you
can find CDs featuring a mix of some of your favorite music stars
behind the counter at McDonald's restaurants. Customers who buy a
regularly priced Mickey D's item can add one of the three CDs or a
video to their orders for $4.99 each. Look for acts like Britney
Spears, 'N Sync, Joe, Q-Tip, Sisqo and Enrique Iglesias. They'll be
available until Aug. 24 or while supplies last.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
