<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ ``I AM NOT SUPERWOMAN!''
Gail yells into the phone plastered against my ear. ``A pox upon
Martha Stewart!'' Rather than ask what has tilted her day into a
spell of the nasties, I join in. ``YEAH! And Helen Trent and Our
Gal Sunday, too!'' The Cape Cod end of the connection falls silent
for a just a second while she thinks that one over. ``Who's that?''
she asks. I knew she would. Gail's 12 years younger than I am.
(Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ It was early in the a.m. and
something woke me. A sound. The faint plastic-on-plastic tap of
computer keys. It was only my daughter reacting to a federal court
order. Knowing she had only a day left to use Napster, she was up
late downloading the last few songs. Around the planet, a record
number of computer users were hooked up to Napster. (Lane, Daytona
Beach News-Journal) MOVED.
