<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-COLUMN (Undated) _ At this stage of the presidential
marathon, George W. Bush appears able and ready for the final
three-month stretch; Al Gore does not. By Robert A. Jordan.
</P>
<P>
   OLIPHANT-COLUMN (Conshohocken, Pa.) _ As it turns out, Al Gore
is a tad on the old side of typical. George W. Bush is going to be
a lot less typical. By Thomas Oliphant.
</P>
