<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`SPACE JAM' SCORES AGAIN ON DVD 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Space Jam'' (DVD) _ The Michael Jordan, Bugs
Bunny, and Daffy Duck movie was released on VHS last year, but the
DVD has added some amusing features. The alternate track
commentary, particularly the remarks by Bunny and Duck complaining
about their roles, is as funny as anything in the film. The problem
is that the voice talent and other commentators keep repeating the
difficulties of working with digital effects. Who cares? Give us
more of the animated cast's complaints.
</P>
<P>
   ``Intimate Lighting'' _ While the French New Wave garnered most
of the publicity, the influential East European independent cinema
has had a comparable effect on film history. In this Ivan Passer
1965 release, the story of two musicians is equally comic and
tragic. Filled with marvelous political metaphors and
anti-totalitarian symbols, Passer's work showed that making films
about everyday people can make for extraordinary movies.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   POIROT RETURNS: On Tuesday, Acorn Media will release the fifth
three-volume boxed set of ``Agatha Christie's Poirot'' from the PBS
``Mystery!'' series, which subsequently ran on A &AMP; E. Originally
shown on British television, ``Poirot'' features David Suchet with
Hugh Fraser and Pauline Moran. This set sells for $39.95.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``THE FLY'' FLIES: On Sept. 5, Fox will release ``The Fly''
(1958) and ``Return of the Fly'' (1959), both starring Vincent
Price as the mad scientist, and ``The Fly'' (1986) and ``The Fly
II'' (1989), the remakes of the originals. Each set will be issued
as a double feature on DVD for $34.98 and $14.98 on VHS.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Aug. 8: ``Reindeer Games,'' ``Titus'' (DVD),
``Holy Smoke,'' ``The Grandfather,'' ``The Beatles Collection''
(DVD), ``Brian's Song'' (DVD), ``Cat Ballou: Special Edition''
(DVD), ``A Map of the World,'' ``Jerry and Tom.'' Aug. 15: ``Erin
Brockovich'' (DVD), ``It's the Rage,'' ``Grey Owl,'' ``Ghost Dog''
(DVD). Aug. 22: ``The Tigger Movie'' (DVD), ``Mifune.'' Aug. 29:
``I Dreamed of Africa'' (DVD). Sept. 5: ``The Unknown Jonathan
Winters'' (DVD), ``The Unknown Peter Sellers'' (DVD).
</P>
