   ISRAEL-POLITICS (Jerusalem) _ Prime Minister Ehud Barak won a
no-confidence vote in parliament Monday, after parliament elected a
member of the opposition Likud party, Moshe Katzav, as Israel's new
president, rejecting Shimon Peres. By John Kifner.
</P>
<P>
