   CVN-LAURA-BUSH (Philadephia) _ The first lady of Texas, Laura
Bush, has been described as ``traditional,'' ``shy'' and
``reluctant.'' But after a year on the campaign trail, she's come
into her own as the candidate's wife focused on education. Despite
a small case of butterflies, she steps into the limelight as one of
the main speakers at the Republican National Convention's opening
night. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
