<P>
   SCI-ARTHRITIS (Undated) _ A component of marijuana -- not the
part that makes people high -- slows the attack of rheumatoid
arthritis in mice. Researchers hope they can take the compound to
human trials without legal or political consequences, because the
psychoactive properties of marijuana are not involved. By Richard
Saltus. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-DEAD-BIRDS (Boston) _ So many dead birds have been discovered
by residents statewide worried about the West Nile virus, state
officials hire a courier service to start picking them all up. But
an important point is being lost: You have more chance of being hit
by a Mack truck then ever contracting the disease. By Beth Daley.
900 words.
