<P>
   TV-BETTE MIDLER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ TV series built around big-name stars are,
from the start, developed differently, and that's the problem.
Instead of beginning with an idea or premise and then working
toward the casting and the development of good scripts, networks
often start with an established star and work ``backward'' toward
the idea. It often means disaster. By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story has
moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FALL TV-NO BUZZ &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ Buzz concerning the upcoming fall TV season
will have to be manufactured because for the first time in a long
time all the buzz is about the lack of buzz. Of the 30 or so pilots
screened over the 12-day network portion of the Critics Press Tour,
only two showed promise. By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
