<P>
   GOP-RDP-NYT (Philadelphia) _ A convention roundup: Republicans
open their convention, beginning what party leaders hope will be a
highly scripted four- day celebration of George W. Bush; the first
real business came when the delegates approved a platform that
reaffirms the party's staunch position opposing abortion while
adopting Bush's compassionate conservative positions; according to
a New York Times/CBS News poll of delegates, the Republicans here
are far more conservative than average Republican voters, but Karl
Rove, the chief strategist for the Bush Campaign, played down the
dichotomy between the delegates and the message in an interview
Monday.
