<HEADLINE>
BARGAINS ON SEA ISLAND, IN YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK, PUERTO RICO
AND BRITISH COLUMBIA 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sunday, August 6)  
 By JOSEPH SIANO   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   GEORGIA SAVINGS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The beachfront Cloister on Sea Island, Ga., is offering summer
rates from Aug. 15 to Sept. 26 of $204 a person a night, double
occupancy. Guests receive the best room available at check-in, so
savings can range from $50 to $200 a night. The rate is good Sunday
through Wednesday and includes three meals a day. Guests under 19
sharing a room with their parents stay and eat free. Through Labor
Day, parents can enjoy free time while children ages 3 through 12
partake of the Junior Staff program, which includes field trips,
tennis lessons and other activities. Golfers can also get unlimited
greens fees at three courses with cart and range balls for $113 a
day; one course requires hiring a caddie, at an extra charge. For
information and reservations, contact (800) 732-4752.
</P>
<P>
   YELLOWSTONE AUTUMN
</P>
<P>
   The National Park Lodges in Yellowstone are offering a series of
autumn specials for those who book online at
www.travelyellowstone &QC; .com. The room rates at the lodges, operated
by Amfac Parks and Resorts, have been reduced by an average of 35
percent. At the Lake Yellowstone Hotel, a premium room is $99 Oct.
1 to 5; the Old Faithful Snow Lodge has a Lodge room for the same
price Oct. 8 to 14. At Grant Village, a midrange room is $69 and a
high-range room $79 from Sept. 24 to 30. From Oct. 1 to 9 at the
Mammoth Hot Springs Hotel, a room with shared bath is $25, a room
with private bath is $59 and a suite is $149.
</P>
<P>
   FERRY BARGAINS
</P>
<P>
   For self-drive tours of the Inside Passage along the British
Columbia coast, the fall may be the time to go. BC Ferries is
offering a discounted transportation and accommodations package for
its 15-hour cruises from Port Hardy to Prince Rupert from Sept. 17
through Oct. 14. The daylight voyages offer views of snowcapped
mountains, forested hills, fjords and sheltered coastal villages.
Prices start at $170 a person, double occupancy, and include
one-way passage for one car and two adults and two nights' lodging
at a choice of 19 motels and hotels near BC Ferries ports. Rates
represent a 20 percent discount in ferry fares and up to 40 percent
off the peak rates for lodging. To book, call (800) 435-5622.
</P>
<P>
   EARLY-BIRD SPECIAL
</P>
<P>
   For guests who don't mind helping a new resort work the kinks
out, there's the Debut Getaway at the Ocean Villas, a new addition
to the Westin Rio Mar Beach on Puerto Rico. From the scheduled
opening date of Oct. 1 through Dec. 21, two-bedroom oceanfront
villas (accommodating up to six people) will cost $2,000 for four
nights if guests arrive Saturday through Wednesday; guests arriving
Thursday or Friday pay the same price for three nights. It includes
two rounds of golf per villa at the resort's two courses, two hours
of tennis and $200 in food credits. The potential saving is about
$1,000. Taxes are included and the offer is subject to
availability. Call (800) 937-8461.
</P>
